CONTENT: Thank you so much for the opportunity.

CONVERSATION TITLE: An ML aware and centric data visualization platform
SUBJECT: An ML aware and centric data visualization platform
CONTENT: Hi Nikhil,  Interactive data visualization platforms have not historically been built for ML.  They are good at data aggregation, but lack model awareness and stop short of root cause analysis within the analytics tool.  Arize brings analytics into the age of ML for monitoring and observability, resulting in improved performance of models in production.   If you are interested, when would be a good time to connect live and learn more?  Best,   Rasam

Thanks a lot Nikhil, that was very insightful and will help me a lot to take a decision.

1. RIT is famous and well known for computing sciences. I like the curriculum of it. I felt the structure of the courses was really good. Electives and all. Also RIT coop program is good. These were the reasons for me to come to RIT 2. I did not get any TA/RA position. RIT is not a research oriented university. So not a lot of RA positions. You get a lot TA positions in Information science department. But it will be a bit difficult as we are from other major. But we can get them. Other part time are dining jobs for first semester. You can start applying for desk jobs later in 2nd semester. 3. Personally, I like the course a lot. Theres only one course which i found a bit different from data Science career path. Rest of them are good. Electives and all as I said are pretty good. Lot of diverse options. 4. If you keep your financials correct, it’ll be 100% 5. You get a lot of unofficial WhatsApp groups where u can decide housing.  6 and 7. Internships coops and full times should be applied online. That is everywhere. You don’t get any assistance from any university.  8. You will have a course named software construction which is on java. It’ll be from basic java to advanced java. So its better to learn and practice till data structures in java before you come here. Also basic python.

Since you asked about my experience in UJM, I would like to explain it in two categories. PROS: You get a decent education in Machine learning and data mining  Professors are well qualified and have many years of experience in this field. If you are interested, you can even propose to work in the labs.  For most of the courses, you will have practical assignments as well as written exams. Your workload gets shared.  You can go for an exchange program in the second year to countries like Germany, the Netherlands, Belgium and so on.  As you may know, the cost of living in the city is cheaper than in many other cities in France.  CONS: As I said earlier that the professors are well qualified, You will still find it a little difficult to follow the lectures because they are always taught at a very high level. You must try to do pre-study the topics before attending any lecture.  For some of the courses, I personally find that there is so much of a gap between the theory and the practicals. This is my opinion. It might not be correct as well.  As most of the projects and practical assignments are designed in a such way that it can only be done in a team of 3 or 4. Your main challenge will be to find a good team who are willing to work.  Semesters are too short. You have to be a quick learner.  Overall, I would rate UJM as 5/10. For the money you afford, you get a decent education. Honestly, when you compare the standard of education in Germany, UJM standards are not so great!!😊 All the best

Hi, Nikhil!


Data is reshaping business operations. A data-Driven culture is the focus of modern age organizations. It is time for you now to level up with the world.


The 2-year MBA (Data Science) Program at SRM University AP is specially designed for working professionals to give a holistic understanding of data science & ML-AI and aims to hone cross-functional management skills amongst individuals. The main focus of the program is to impart experiential learning

and foster knowledge through real-life case studies. The

curriculum is divided into 1700+ Hours of interactive learning with 60% hands-on practical projects & 40% theory. With our CareerNxt portal and specialized guidance for each aspirant, we offer 360-degree career planning and job search support.


-Highly Acclaimed MBA (Data Science)

degree from SRM University AP with the latest Data Science Curriculum specially designed for managers and leaders

- Data Science Industry Experienced Faculty with IIT and Global University Pedigree

- Curriculum with emerging technologies like applications of Machine Learning, advanced Deep Learning, Artificial Intelligence, Natural Language Processing, best practices in data visualization, and the art of storytelling

- Exposure to a full-fledged capstone project for real-life experience in numerous applications of data science across domains and functions such as finance, HR, healthcare, and supply chain

- Experiential Learning through case materials and simulations from Harvard Business Publishing

- Alumni status of SRM University AP with free access to private online & offline networking events

- 2-month internship with corporate partners for real-life experience

- High Impact Career Services and Placement Assistance through CareerNxt Platform.

- lifetime access to AI-based LMS StudyNxt to access the course materials, engaging videos, projects, and class recordings



Who should take this course?


Anyone with a bachelor's degree with a minimum of 50% in 10th, 12th, and Graduation.

Working Professionals with 2+ years of experience willing to upskill and move

to leadership roles.

Graduates working in the Data Science industry and IT professionals.

Entry-level programmers in the IT field who are looking for a career transition into Data Science.

Hello Nikhil,


I am excited to announce our latest applied learning program, Crio Launch, for final and pre-final year Student Developers. In Crio Launch, you get an internship-like experience of building real software products, and learn the right skills to launch your career in tech. Oh btw, you pay nothing :)


The program has already seen over 8000 applicants from across the country, and this number is growing rapidly. Don't miss out. Application deadline is 20th January 2020.


Here are some more details, 


What will you build?


QMoney

  • Seen complex charts and stock market data on finance sites? Have you thought about simplifying it for users? Build QMoney, a personal stock portfolio analysis and recommendations platform
  • Concepts Covered: Language (Java), Databases (MySQL), OOPs, Developer Tools, Developer Practices

QStore

  • Wonder how and where complex data structures and algorithms get used? Learn more when you build QStore, a customised product data store for an e-commerce platform
  • Concepts Covered: Applied Data Structures, Algorithms 

QBox

  • From the days of FTP to Dropbox, file-sharing has been a fascinating problem with several different use-cases. Build QBox, a secured file sharing solution for enterprise networks
  • Concepts Covered: Linux, OS & Networking Foundations, Scripting


How is the program delivered?

  • Crio Launch is a 8-10 week online (remote) program starting in the last week of January 2020
  • You will spend around 15 hours a week to achieve the program milestones
  • If you get stuck, you can access our slack workspace and get guidance from Crio Tech Leads and other developers in the community


Excited? To know the other benefits of the program, and to apply for the program, click here.


Looking forward to your participation.


Regards,

Rathinamurthy

Co-Founder | Crio.Do
